Parses `docs/STATUS.md`'s backlog table and resolves a free-text request into a formatted TASK ITEM, or falls back to the raw request if nothing matches.

The table format is fixed: GFM pipe table with columns `task | description | impact | difficulty`, header and separator rows skipped by `is_header`/`is_separator`. Cell splitting (`split_row` via `split_unescaped_pipes`) treats `\|` as an escaped literal pipe, not a delimiter — any code producing STATUS.md rows with literal `|` in a cell must escape it this way or parsing breaks. Leading/trailing empty cells (from the table's outer `|`) are stripped before the 4-column conversion.

Matching (`matching_rows`) is case-insensitive substring match of `request` against the `task` column only, trimmed and lowercased. `resolve(status, request) -> Result<String, BriefError>` returns: raw trimmed request on zero matches, formatted `TASK:/DESCRIPTION:/IMPACT:/DIFFICULTY:` block on exactly one match, `BriefError::AmbiguousItem` (listing all matched tasks as `- task`) on multiple. `matched(status, request) -> bool` exposes whether at least one row matched, using the identical substring rule, so callers can distinguish "genuine match" from "fallback to raw text" without re-deriving the rule.

`parse_rows` is public and order-preserving; row order in the output matches row order in the source document, which matters for deterministic ambiguity-error listings.